        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1666624409" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16829969036075464884">The final novel in a trilogy about the ending of a monstrous war, WWI, supposedly the War to End All Wars. My husband and I listened to it on our recent trip. Given some of the more graphic descriptions of human depravity I don’t recommend the audio version. You can more easily skim over sections you don’t care to read with a written text v. an audio book. Undoubtedly it would have helped if we’d read the first two books, but it has made me more curious to read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11837308.The_Guns_of_August_The_Proud_Tower' title='The Guns of August/The Proud Tower by Barbara W. Tuchman' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Guns of August/The Proud Tower</a></span>
  <span id="freeText16829969036075464884" style="display:none">The final novel in a trilogy about the ending of a monstrous war, WWI, supposedly the War to End All Wars. My husband and I listened to it on our recent trip. Given some of the more graphic descriptions of human depravity I don’t recommend the audio version. You can more easily skim over sections you don’t care to read with a written text v. an audio book. Undoubtedly it would have helped if we’d read the first two books, but it has made me more curious to read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11837308.The_Guns_of_August_The_Proud_Tower" title="The Guns of August/The Proud Tower by Barbara W. Tuchman" rel="nofollow noopener">The Guns of August/The Proud Tower</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/355697.All_Quiet_on_the_Western_Front" title="All Quiet on the Western Front by Erich Maria Remarque" rel="nofollow noopener">All Quiet on the Western Front</a> by way of comparison. <br /><br /> </span>
