  <span id="freeText5389819299844700775" style="display:none">Shattering. Just shattering. I felt the hairs on the back of my neck rise as I reached the last pages of this book. <br /><br />I don't have time to write a proper review right now--for that, I point you to Sckenda's extremely excellent review, the one that inspired me to read the <i>Regeneration</i> trilogy. <br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/317565510?book_show_action=false&amp;page=1">https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a><br /><br />Seems fitting to read it this summer, which marks 100 years since the beginning of this awesomely destructive, breathtakingly stupid and poorly-prosecuted war.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /> <br /><br /></span>
