<span id="freeTextContainer9587858629753099967">Pat Barker was born in Thornaby-on-Tees in 1943. She was educated at the London School of Economics and has been a teacher of history and politics. <br/><br/>Her books include the highly acclaimed Regeneration trilogy <i>Regeneration</i>; <i>The Eye in the Door</i>, winner of the Guardian Fiction Prize; and <i>The Ghost Road</i>, winner of the Booker Prize; as well as seven other novels. She&apos;s married and lives in Durham, Engla</span>
  <span id="freeText9587858629753099967" style="display:none">Pat Barker was born in Thornaby-on-Tees in 1943. She was educated at the London School of Economics and has been a teacher of history and politics. <br /><br />Her books include the highly acclaimed Regeneration trilogy <i>Regeneration</i>; <i>The Eye in the Door</i>, winner of the Guardian Fiction Prize; and <i>The Ghost Road</i>, winner of the Booker Prize; as well as seven other novels. She's married and lives in Durham, England. </span>
